More than four million people have now fled Ukraine for neighbouring countries amidst the Russian invasion that began on February 24, 2022. However, black and brown students who have fled, have been detained by EU border authorities in what has been condemned as "clearly discriminatory" and "not acceptable", reports Democracy Now. Despite assurances from the European governments that it would provide swift protection to those fleeing Ukraine, non-European asylum-seekers continue to face violence at the EU's borders, write Emily Venturi and Anna Iasmi Vallianatou for Chatham House.